const faqSchema={"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "Do I really need a real estate agent to buy my first home?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "While legally you could buy without an agent, having buyer representation is strongly recommended for first-time purchases. Your buyer's agent costs you nothing (seller pays commission), provides crucial market knowledge, handles negotiations, and guides you through complex paperwork. Agents who specialize in first-time buyers educate while representing your interests. The mistakes prevented and better deals negotiated typically far exceed any perceived savings of going without representation."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How do I know if a lender is trustworthy?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Look for lenders with strong online reviews, proper licensing, and willingness to educate without pressure. Trustworthy lenders explain all your options including pros and cons, provide clear fee disclosures, and don't push you toward products that don't fit. Ask for references from recent first-time buyers. At Stairway Mortgage, we focus on education-first approach and building long-term relationships, not just closing loans quickly."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can my parents help me buy without being on the loan?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, parents can provide gift funds for down payment and closing costs without being co-borrowers. They'll need to sign a gift letter stating the money is a gift requiring no repayment, and lender will document the transfer. This allows you to buy in your name alone while benefiting from family assistance. Review complete gift fund requirements to understand proper documentation process."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What's the difference between pre-qualification and pre-approval?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Pre-qualification is rough estimate based on information you provide without verification. Pre-approval involves actual documentation review, credit check, and preliminary underwriting approval. For first-time buyers, proper pre-approval is essential\u2014sellers and agents take you seriously, you know exactly what you can afford, and you identify problems before finding your dream home. Always get pre-approved before seriously shopping."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are down payment assistance programs hard to qualify for?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Many first-time buyers assume they won't qualify for assistance and don't even apply. Reality is these programs are designed specifically to help people like you. Income limits are often generous (many allow up to 80-140% of area median income), credit requirements are typically moderate, and homebuyer education courses are usually the main requirement. Start by researching down payment assistance options in your state\u2014you might be surprised by your eligibility."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What's Next in Your Journey?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Continue building your Smart Stewards foundation:"}}]};
