   <div class="post-main">
    <article class="prose-editorial post-body" set:html={`<h2><b>First Time Home Buyer Assistance and How to Build Your Support Team</b></h2><p>Whether you're a young adult navigating your first home purchase or a parent helping guide the process, knowing who to turn to and where to find help transforms an overwhelming journey into a manageable one. The difference between buyers who succeed and those who struggle isn't luck—it's having the right team and resources.</p><p>In this guide, you'll discover:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Who should be on your first-time buyer team and what each person does</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Where to find down payment assistance programs in your area (<a href="https://www.hud.gov/">according to HUD resources</a>)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">How to identify trustworthy professionals who understand your generation</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Free resources and tools that guide you through each step</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Red flags that warn you away from predatory advice or services</li></ul><p>The young adults achieving homeownership in their twenties aren't doing it alone—they're building strategic support networks that guide them through the complexity.</p><p>Ready to build your first-time buyer team?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to connect with professionals who specialize in helping young adults achieve homeownership.</p><h2><b>Who Actually Needs to Be On Your Team?</b></h2><p><b>Here's what stops many first-time buyers:</b> They either try to navigate everything alone and get overwhelmed, or they involve too many people and get conflicting advice. The right team has specific roles that work together.</p><p><b>Essential team members for every first-time buyer:</b></p><p><b>Mortgage Loan Officer (First Person to Contact):</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Determines what you can afford before you shop</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Explains loan programs and down payment options</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Provides pre-approval letter for offers</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Guides documentation and qualification process</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Coordinates closing timeline</li></ul><p><b>Real Estate Agent (Buyer's Agent):</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Shows properties matching your criteria and budget</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Provides market knowledge and neighborhood insights</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Writes and negotiates offers on your behalf</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Recommends inspectors and other vendors</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Guides you through contract and closing</li></ul><p><b>Home Inspector:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Evaluates property condition before purchase</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Identifies problems you can't see</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Provides detailed report on all systems</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Helps you make informed buying decision</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">May save you from costly mistakes</li></ul><p><b>Optional but helpful team members:</b></p><p><b>Real Estate Attorney:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Reviews contracts in attorney-review states</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Protects your legal interests</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Handles title issues if they arise</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Required in some states, optional in others</li></ul><p><b>Insurance Agent:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Provides homeowners insurance quotes</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Explains coverage options</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Bundles policies for savings</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Required for closing</li></ul><p><b>The coordination advantage:</b> When your team members work together and communicate, the process flows smoothly. When they don't know each other, gaps emerge and things fall through cracks.</p><p>Use the<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/fha-loan/"> FHA loan program</a> designed specifically for first-time buyers with minimal down payment requirements and flexible qualification.</p><p><img src="/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ChatGPT-Image-Nov-6-2025-01_07_00-AM.png" /></p><h2><b>Where Do You Find Down Payment Assistance Programs?</b></h2><p><b>This is where thousands of dollars in help hide in plain sight.</b> Most first-time buyers don't know these programs exist or how to find them—yet they're specifically designed to help people like you.</p><p><b>Down payment assistance sources by level:</b></p><p><b>State Housing Finance Agencies:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Every state has housing finance agency</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Offer down payment grants and forgivable loans</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Income limits based on area median income</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">First-time buyer specific programs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Search "[Your State] Housing Finance Agency"</li></ul><p><b>County and City Programs:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Local government assistance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Often more generous than state programs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">May have neighborhood targeting</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Sometimes forgivable after occupancy period</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Check county/city housing department websites</li></ul><p><b>National Programs:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Chenoa Fund (nationwide FHA assistance)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">NACA (Neighborhood Assistance Corporation)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Habitat for Humanity homeownership</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Good Neighbor Next Door (teachers, law enforcement, firefighters, EMTs)</li></ul><p><b>Employer Programs:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Some employers offer home buying assistance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Especially hospitals, schools, corporations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">May be grants or forgivable loans</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Check with HR benefits department</li></ul><p><b>Where to search:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">HUD Local Office locator</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Down Payment Resource database</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">State housing finance agency websites</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Your lender (we track all available programs)</li></ul><p><b>The layering strategy:</b> Many buyers combine multiple programs—state assistance plus local program plus employer benefit. Each program has rules, but they often stack to cover entire down payment.</p><p>Explore comprehensive<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/down-payment-assistance/"> down payment assistance programs</a> and see this<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/down-payment-assistance/"> case study</a> of a teacher who used grant funding.</p><h2><b>How Do You Find a Good Real Estate Agent for First-Timers?</b></h2><p><b>Not all agents understand first-time buyers—especially young adults with different priorities than traditional buyers.</b> The right agent makes the process educational; the wrong one makes it stressful.</p><p><b>Qualities to look for in first-time buyer agents:</b></p><p><b>Experience with Your Demographic:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Works with buyers in twenties and early thirties regularly</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Understands modern communication preferences</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Patient explaining process step-by-step</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Comfortable with questions at every stage</li></ul><p><b>Knowledge of Entry-Level Markets:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Focuses on price range you can afford</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Knows neighborhoods appealing to young adults</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Understands multi-unit and house hacking strategies</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Can identify value properties needing work</li></ul><p><b>Strong Lender Relationships:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Works with lenders who understand first-time buyers</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Communicates well throughout process</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Coordinates timelines effectively</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Doesn't cause delays through poor communication</li></ul><p><b>Where to find qualified agents:</b></p><p><b>Ask Your Lender for Referrals:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Lenders know which agents work well with first-timers</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Have seen agents through multiple transactions</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Know who communicates and closes deals</li></ul><p><b>Interview Multiple Agents:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Meet with at least three before choosing</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Ask about experience with first-time buyers</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Discuss communication style and expectations</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Check references from recent first-time buyer clients</li></ul><p><b>Red flags to avoid:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Pressure to buy quickly without education</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Dismissive of your questions or concerns</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Focuses only on most expensive homes</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Poor communication or slow response times</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Doesn't explain documents or process</li></ul><p>See how working with experienced<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/resources/"> real estate professionals</a> helps first-time buyers navigate the purchase process successfully.</p><p><img src="/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ChatGPT-Image-Nov-6-2025-01_07_04-AM.png" /></p><h2><b>What Free Resources Actually Help First-Time Buyers?</b></h2><p><b>You don't need to pay for most home buying education—legitimate free resources exist everywhere.</b> Knowing where to find them prevents expensive mistakes and predatory services.</p><p><b>Free educational resources:</b></p><p><b>HUD-Approved Housing Counseling:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Free one-on-one counseling</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Certified housing counselors</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Budget analysis and planning</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Down payment assistance guidance</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Find at HUD.gov counseling locator</li></ul><p><b>First-Time Buyer Classes:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Many cities offer free classes</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">State housing agencies provide education</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Some lenders offer buyer seminars</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">May satisfy requirements for some assistance programs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Usually evening or weekend sessions</li></ul><p><b>Online Calculators and Tools:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Mortgage payment calculators</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Affordability calculators</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Amortization schedules</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Rent vs buy comparisons</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Available on lender websites</li></ul><p><b>Government Websites:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">HUD First-Time Buyer resources</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Fannie Mae HomePath</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Freddie Mac CreditSmart</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Your state housing finance agency</li></ul><p><b>The education advantage:</b> Buyers who complete housing counseling or education courses often qualify for better loan terms, lower down payments, or reduced mortgage insurance. The time investment pays dividends.</p><p><b>What to avoid paying for:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Lists of "secret" programs (they're public)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Overpriced buyer courses when free ones exist</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"Guaranteed approval" services</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Advance fee loan scams</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Credit repair that promises illegal actions</li></ul><p>Use comprehensive calculators at<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculators/"> Stairway Mortgage</a> to model different home buying scenarios and understand costs before shopping.</p><h2><b>How Do Parents Best Help Without Taking Over?</b></h2><p><b>This balance challenges families constantly:</b> Parents want to help their young adult children, but taking over prevents the learning that builds competence. The right approach empowers without hovering.</p><p><b>Healthy parental assistance strategies:</b></p><p><b>Financial Support:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Gift funds for down payment (properly documented)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Co-signing if needed (understanding the commitment)</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Helping with moving costs or furniture</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Emergency fund contribution for homeownership</li></ul><p><b>Knowledge and Experience:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Share your own home buying experiences</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Attend showings if invited</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Review contracts together</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Help evaluate neighborhoods</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Provide perspective without dictating</li></ul><p><b>Emotional Support:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Encouragement through stressful moments</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Reality check when needed</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Celebrating milestones</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Backup plan if things don't work out</li></ul><p><b>What not to do as parents:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Make decisions your adult child should make</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Contact professionals directly without permission</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Override your child's preferences with yours</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Use financial help as control mechanism</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Criticize every home they like</li></ul><p><b>For young adults working with parents:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Be clear about what help you want</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Set boundaries about decision-making</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Keep parents informed but maintain control</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Appreciate their experience while owning your choice</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Establish your adult relationship through this process</li></ul><p>Review<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/blog/gift-money/"> gift fund guidelines</a> showing how parents can properly assist with down payment while following lender requirements.</p><p><img src="/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ChatGPT-Image-Nov-6-2025-01_07_08-AM.png" /></p><h2><b>What Questions Should You Ask Every Professional?</b></h2><p><b>The right questions reveal whether professionals understand first-time buyers or just see you as a transaction.</b> These questions separate experts from order-takers.</p><p><b>Questions for mortgage lenders:</b></p><p><b>About Programs:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What loan programs work best for first-time buyers in my situation?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How much down payment do I actually need?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What down payment assistance programs am I eligible for?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"Can you explain the difference between these options?"</li></ul><p><b>About Process:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What documentation will I need to provide?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How long does approval typically take?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What could prevent my approval?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How do you communicate throughout the process?"</li></ul><p><b>About Experience:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How many first-time buyers do you work with?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"Can you provide references from recent first-time buyer clients?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What's your approach to helping young adults buy homes?"</li></ul><p><b>Questions for real estate agents:</b></p><p><b>About Market:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What neighborhoods have you seen first-time buyers succeed in?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What's realistic for my budget in current market?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How competitive is the market I'm targeting?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What strategies help first-time buyers win in this market?"</li></ul><p><b>About Properties:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What should I prioritize in my first home?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How do you evaluate good value versus overpriced?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What red flags should I watch for?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What mistakes do you see first-time buyers make?"</li></ul><p><b>About Process:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How many showings before buyers typically find their home?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What happens after we make an offer?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"How do you guide through inspection negotiations?"</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">"What does typical timeline look like?"</li></ul><p><b>The professional's response matters as much as the answer:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Do they take time to educate or rush to close you?</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Are they patient with questions or dismissive?</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Do they explain in terms you understand?</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Do they seem genuinely invested in your success?</li></ul><p><img src="/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ChatGPT-Image-Nov-6-2025-01_10_50-AM.png" /></p><h2><b>How Stairway Mortgage Serves as Your Central Resource</b></h2><p><b>We understand that first-time buyers need more than just a mortgage—they need guidance, education, and connections to build their complete team.</b> Our approach makes us your home base throughout the journey.</p><p><b>Our comprehensive support:</b></p><p><b>Pre-Purchase Education:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Explain process from start to finish</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Calculate what you can afford</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Identify down payment assistance you qualify for</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Discuss realistic timeline to homeownership</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Answer all questions without pressure</li></ul><p><b>Team Building:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Refer you to experienced first-time buyer agents</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Connect you with trusted inspectors and vendors</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Coordinate communication across all team members</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Serve as central point of contact</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Ensure everyone works toward same goal</li></ul><p><b>Program Navigation:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Research all assistance programs available</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Help you apply for grants and programs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Coordinate multiple funding sources</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Maximize your benefits through program stacking</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Handle all lender-side documentation</li></ul><p><b>Ongoing Guidance:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Available throughout shopping and offer process</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Review contracts and timelines</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Problem-solve challenges that arise</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Coordinate closing timeline</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Support you through final steps</li></ul><p>Ready to start building your first-time buyer team?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to begin with expert mortgage guidance and referrals to other professionals you'll need.</p><h2><b>Ready to Stop Feeling Overwhelmed and Start Moving Forward?</b></h2><p><b>You've learned who needs to be on your team, where to find assistance, and how to identify trustworthy professionals.</b> The difference between buyers who succeed and those who give up isn't capability—it's having the right support system.</p><p><b>Your next steps:</b></p><ol><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Contact Mortgage Lender First</b>: Get pre-qualified and understand your options</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Find Real Estate Agent</b>: Interview agents experienced with first-time buyers</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Research Assistance</b>: Identify programs you might qualify for</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Get Educated</b>: Take advantage of free counseling and resources</li></ol><p><b>Different paths work for different people:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Some build their team quickly and move fast</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Others take time researching and learning first</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Many involve parents strategically for support</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">All succeed by surrounding themselves with experts</li></ul><p>The young adults achieving homeownership in their twenties aren't figuring everything out alone. They're building teams, leveraging assistance programs, and accepting help while maintaining ownership of their journey.</p><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Get pre-approved</a> to start your journey with expert guidance, or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/"> take our discovery quiz</a> to see which path fits your situation best.</p><h2><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b></h2><h3><b>Do I really need a real estate agent to buy my first home?</b></h3><p>While legally you could buy without an agent, having buyer representation is strongly recommended for first-time purchases. Your buyer's agent costs you nothing (seller pays commission), provides crucial market knowledge, handles negotiations, and guides you through complex paperwork. Agents who specialize in first-time buyers educate while representing your interests. The mistakes prevented and better deals negotiated typically far exceed any perceived savings of going without representation.</p><h3><b>How do I know if a lender is trustworthy?</b></h3><p>Look for lenders with strong online reviews, proper licensing, and willingness to educate without pressure. Trustworthy lenders explain all your options including pros and cons, provide clear fee disclosures, and don't push you toward products that don't fit. Ask for references from recent first-time buyers. At<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/about/"> Stairway Mortgage</a>, we focus on education-first approach and building long-term relationships, not just closing loans quickly.</p><h3><b>Can my parents help me buy without being on the loan?</b></h3><p>Yes, parents can provide gift funds for down payment and closing costs without being co-borrowers. They'll need to sign a gift letter stating the money is a gift requiring no repayment, and lender will document the transfer. This allows you to buy in your name alone while benefiting from family assistance. Review complete<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/blog/gift-money/"> gift fund requirements</a> to understand proper documentation process.</p><h3><b>What's the difference between pre-qualification and pre-approval?</b></h3><p>Pre-qualification is rough estimate based on information you provide without verification. Pre-approval involves actual documentation review, credit check, and preliminary underwriting approval. For first-time buyers, proper pre-approval is essential—sellers and agents take you seriously, you know exactly what you can afford, and you identify problems before finding your dream home. Always get pre-approved before seriously shopping.</p><h3><b>Are down payment assistance programs hard to qualify for?</b></h3><p>Many first-time buyers assume they won't qualify for assistance and don't even apply. Reality is these programs are designed specifically to help people like you. Income limits are often generous (many allow up to 80-140% of area median income), credit requirements are typically moderate, and homebuyer education courses are usually the main requirement. Start by researching<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/down-payment-assistance/"> down payment assistance options</a> in your state—you might be surprised by your eligibility.</p><h3><b>Also Helpful for Smart Stewards</b></h3><p><b>Related Resources:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">All Available Loan Programs</a> - Explore first-time buyer options</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/down-payment-assistance/">Down Payment Assistance</a> - Find grants and programs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/fha-loan/">FHA Loans</a> - Popular first-time buyer choice</li></ul><h3><b>What's Next in Your Journey?</b></h3><p>Continue building your Smart Stewards foundation:</p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Home Purchase Budget (Post #13) - 2-year roadmap planning</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">Buying Your First Home (Post #14) - Success stories from young adults</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">House Hacking for Beginners (Post #15) - Eliminate housing costs</li></ul><h3><b>Explore Your Complete Options</b></h3><p><b>Calculate Your Scenarios:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculators/fha-loan/">FHA Loan Calculator</a> - See first-time buyer costs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculators/conventional-loan/">Conventional Loan Calculator</a> - Compare programs</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculators/">All Calculators</a> - Model every scenario</li></ul><p><b>See Real Success Stories:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/down-payment-assistance/">Down Payment Assistance Success</a> - Teacher found help</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/fha-loan/">FHA Loan Success</a> - First-time buyer journey</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">All Case Studies</a> - Every path documented</li></ul><p><b>Ready to Take Action:</b></p><ul><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a Call</a> - Build your team</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/">Discovery Quiz</a> - Find your path</li><li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Get Pre-Approved</a> - Start your journey</li></ul>		
